Package external_sort

Provides classes for external sort.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExternalSort<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
    An ExternalSort sorts data elements in ascending order according to the natural ordering of the elements.
    InputBuffer
    An InputBuffer provides access to objects stored in a fixed size byte array.
    OptimizedExternalSort<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
    An OptimizedExternalSort sorts data elements in ascending order according to the natural ordering of the elements.
    OrderedMergeIterator<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
    Given multiple Iterators each of which iterates over elements in ascending order according to the natural ordering of the elements, an OrderedMergeIterator iterates over all of these elements in ascending order.
    OutputBuffer
    An OutputBuffer is an OutputStream that writes data to a fixed size byte array.
    RunReader
    A RunReader reads objects from a run.
    RunWriter<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
    A RunWriter writes objects on a run using an OutputBuffer.
